window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Three years ago, I swore to myself we were done.</p> <p>Since then, Tweetie Sorenson has embraced the professional hockey player bachelor lifestyle—his social media is a highlight reel of clubs, friends, and a never-ending stream of different women.</p> <p>It’s hard to believe he’s the same man who stole my heart the very night we met. With him, everything felt wild, spontaneous, and absolutely perfect. I thought he was my forever.</p> <p>Then, he broke my heart. Or maybe we broke each other’s. Either way, it was over.</p> <p>I’ve moved on—new city, dream job—until my boss throws me back into Tweetie’s world. I’m sent to Chicago to manage the Falcons’ social media, which means working alongside the one man I never truly let go of. FML.</p>"; 
